Before entering into the implementations, I explain two tibble's functions, `enframe()` and `deframe()` briefly. They can convert a vector to/from a two-column data.frame.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tibble)

x <- 1:3
names(x) <- c("foo", "bar", "baz")

enframe(x)
